      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIG ZAG MAN (7) missed the hat-trick last start when fourth and beaten 5.5 lengths (36.81) last time at Nowra. Form at this distance is sound. Should bounce back. ZIPPING MOONEY (6) goes very well this trip starting 11 times for four wins and four minors. Comes off a (35.68) win last time, scoring by a neck in a Grade 4/5 over 622m at this track. Can feature in the finish. WEST ROCK CASEY (4) pinged the lids from the inside draw and led until late, finishing second and beaten a neck (35.70) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 622m. The form out of his last race has been franked. Expected to be in this for a long way. ZIPPING EVANIA (1) has a solid strike rate from this box.",
